/bin/zsh -lc 'td create "Eliminate dynamic atom creation in audit framework validation" -t bug -p P1 --epic td-067a70 --labels "review-finding,security" -d "Audit validation creates atoms from runtime field names, which can exhaust the VM atom table under untrusted/custom framework field input. In app/lib/app/audit.ex:417-420, to_error_atom/1 calls String.to_atom(field) when String.to_existing_atom/1 fails. additional_required_fields comes from persisted config_overrides (app/lib/app/audit.ex:371-374), so new arbitrary field names can force atom creation. Suggested fix: keep error keys as strings (or use a bounded mapping) and avoid String.to_atom/1 on external data paths. Found by: Security, Code Quality, Codex Fresh Eyes." --acceptance "1) No runtime path in audit validation calls String.to_atom/1 on user/config-provided field names. 2) Validation still reports missing-field errors with deterministic keys. 3) Regression test covers unknown additional_required_fields without atom creation."' in /Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit succeeded in 77ms:
