Audit insert path still validates legacy flat framework fields; extension-schema validation is not wired.  
Refs: [audit.ex:24](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/audit.ex:24), [audit.ex:318](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/audit.ex:318)

3. `P1 bug` `td-fd22c4`  
API/OpenAPI contract is still legacy (`user_id`, `phi_accessed`) and does not align to `actor_id` + `extensions`.  
Refs: [audit_log_request.ex:12](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app_web/schemas/audit_log_request.ex:12), [audit_log_response.ex:20](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app_web/schemas/audit_log_response.ex:20), [audit_log_controller.ex:52](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app_web/controllers/api/v1/audit_log_controller.ex:52), [audit_log_json.ex:25](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app_web/controllers/api/v1/audit_log_json.ex:25)

4. `P1 bug` `td-4eb51c`  
Security risk: dynamic atom creation from runtime field names (`String.to_atom/1`) can exhaust VM atom table.  
